{
  "version": 2,
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "8eaff688",
      "title": "Phase 2 Decisions",
      "created": "2026-03-07T19:08:41.051Z",
      "archived": true,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "ed71046f",
          "title": "Data Model Changes",
          "created": "2026-03-07T19:08:49.329Z",
          "archived": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "365c4db1",
              "title": "Drop position field",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:16.895Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Array index IS the display order. recompact() goes away. addItem/moveItem simplify."
            },
            {
              "id": "f72c755e",
              "title": "Drop ordering field",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:16.941Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "No more custom/alpha-asc/alpha-desc on containers. getOrderedChildren() just returns items as-is. Agent sorts on demand via move operations."
            },
            {
              "id": "64167976",
              "title": "Rename notes to body",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:16.980Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Generic free-form content field. Can store bug descriptions, ideas, agent instructions, format guidance. Parent body can instruct agent on how to interpret children."
            },
            {
              "id": "4d9da205",
              "title": "Simplified item schema",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.025Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "{id, title, created, archived, body, children[]}"
            }
          ],
          "body": "These affect Phase 1 code. Must be done before or alongside Phase 2 features."
        },
        {
          "id": "eb0e1b46",
          "title": "View System",
          "created": "2026-03-07T19:08:49.370Z",
          "archived": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "cf06de46",
              "title": "Flat render array",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.065Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Each item: {id, title, depth, descendantCount, hasNotes, notesPreview, created, archived}. Pre-walked to requested depth. Agent indents by depth and appends (N)."
            },
            {
              "id": "390f9e31",
              "title": "Depth model",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.106Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "No flag = item + direct children. --depth N = N levels of full details. --depth 0 = infinite/no cutoff. Items at cutoff show (N) active descendant count."
            },
            {
              "id": "ec4d8be4",
              "title": "Breadcrumbs on focus",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.146Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Focused subtree shows item as root + ancestry breadcrumbs. Presentation at Claude's discretion. Doesn't have to be inline with items."
            },
            {
              "id": "215053f8",
              "title": "Archived excluded by default",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.187Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Active views hide archived. Flag like --include-archived or --archived-only to see them."
            }
          ],
          "body": "get is the universal view command. Flat render array. Breadcrumbs for focus."
        },
        {
          "id": "534624af",
          "title": "Archive Behavior",
          "created": "2026-03-07T19:08:49.410Z",
          "archived": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "d39bd117",
              "title": "Cascade archive",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.227Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Archiving a parent archives all descendants. The whole subtree disappears from active view."
            },
            {
              "id": "f719ed99",
              "title": "Cascade unarchive",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.267Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Symmetrical. Unarchiving restores the whole subtree."
            },
            {
              "id": "90772f1e",
              "title": "Active-only descendant counts",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.307Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "If bugs has 5 children and 2 archived, count shows (3) not (5). Consistent with archived=hidden."
            },
            {
              "id": "af884490",
              "title": "Archived tree position",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.347Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "When viewing archived items, show in original tree structure, not flattened."
            }
          ],
          "body": "Cascade archive/unarchive. Active-only counts. Original tree position for archived views."
        },
        {
          "id": "8a3c00ed",
          "title": "CLI Command Surface",
          "created": "2026-03-07T19:08:49.450Z",
          "archived": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "b89b58ab",
              "title": "get is universal view",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.386Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "get [id] [--depth N] covers all read operations. No separate render/list/dump/view commands."
            },
            {
              "id": "ad235fdb",
              "title": "Aliases",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.427Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "list = get (no args). dump = get --depth 0. children = get <id>. path = get with breadcrumbs only. Same code path, DRY."
            },
            {
              "id": "c8b967cd",
              "title": "New: archive/unarchive",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.467Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "archive <id> and unarchive <id>. Both cascade to descendants."
            },
            {
              "id": "ba72f4b4",
              "title": "Stateless CLI",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.508Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "No persistent working directory. Agent holds context conversationally. Human steers with natural language, agent translates to IDs."
            }
          ],
          "body": "Simplify to get as universal view. Aliases for list/dump/children. New archive/unarchive commands."
        },
        {
          "id": "6d10950b",
          "title": "Philosophy",
          "created": "2026-03-07T19:08:49.490Z",
          "archived": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "14f0c60b",
              "title": "No search command",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.549Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Agent ingests tree via get --depth 0, searches in memory. Burrow is a structured dataset + view renderer, not a query engine."
            },
            {
              "id": "092234b9",
              "title": "Same interface, different strengths",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.589Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Human and agent use identical CLI. Agent advantage: bulk ingest full state, use direct ID commands. Human advantage: natural language via agent."
            },
            {
              "id": "d326666f",
              "title": "Body as agent instructions",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.630Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Parent body can describe schema/purpose of children. Self-documenting tree structures. E.g. 'Store bugs here. Title=description. Body=repro steps.'"
            },
            {
              "id": "3548c8be",
              "title": "No artificial size limits",
              "created": "2026-03-07T19:09:17.668Z",
              "archived": true,
              "children": [],
              "body": "Limit is user's machine. Guardrails warn but don't block. Agent optimizes token consumption with smart depth queries. Can cache shortcuts in its own context."
            }
          ],
          "body": "No search command. Agent ingests + searches in memory. Same interface for humans and agents. Body field as self-documenting structure."
        }
      ],
      "body": "Decisions from discuss-phase session 2026-03-07. Follow up on these during planning and execution."
    },
    {
      "id": "90eb1ae1",
      "title": "v1 Remaining Work",
      "created": "2026-03-08T10:35:07.431Z",
      "archived": true,
      "body": "Phases 3 and 4. Prove the value — make it work, not bulletproof.",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "28a9d397",
          "title": "Phase 4: CLI Pretty-Print Rendering",
          "created": "2026-03-08T10:35:12.498Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "Bake tree visualization into the tool. Default = pretty-printed tree. --json flag for structured data. Faster, consistent, no token waste.",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "eb8c40d0",
          "title": "Move --at flag for reordering",
          "created": "2026-03-08T15:36:32.601Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "Support --at <position> on move command. Without --to, reorders within current parent. With --to, places at specific position in destination. Both flags optional independently.\n\nDefault: if --at is not specified, card is added last (appended to end of children array). This matches current behavior for add and move.",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "3d0b5680",
          "title": "dump command should always use --full --depth 0",
          "created": "2026-03-08T15:40:53.611Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "dump is an alias for read with --full --depth 0 (full tree, full bodies). It's the 'show me everything' command. Currently dump does not pass --full by default — this card tracks adding that.",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "e78542df",
          "title": "get --depth should expand nested children in pretty-print",
          "created": "2026-03-08T15:42:53.336Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "Currently --depth flag doesn't affect pretty-print output — always shows only immediate children. Should render nested tree up to the specified depth level with indentation.",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "e804a55f",
          "title": "archived-only should still show [archived] tag",
          "created": "2026-03-08T15:44:41.425Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "When using --archived-only, cards don't show the [archived] tag. For consistency, the tag should always appear on archived cards regardless of filter mode.",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "92cda4d3",
          "title": "Phase 3: Agent Interface",
          "created": "2026-03-08T10:35:12.461Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "Workflow file + slash commands. /gsd:burrow for natural language, shortcuts for common ops. Depends on phase 2 (complete).",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "d338a013",
          "title": "Render: move count after title, replace dot with ellipsis",
          "created": "2026-03-09T13:28:19.500Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "Change tree line format. Move (N) descendant count right after title (hide when 0). Replace • body indicator with … ellipsis after count. Order of indicators: title → count → ellipsis → [archived] → time. Five combos: 'Title (6) …' (count+body), 'Title (1)' (count only), 'Title …' (body only), 'Title' (neither), 'Title (25) … [archived]' (all indicators).",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "696cc6c6",
          "title": "Agent: translate natural language positions to 0-based --at index",
          "created": "2026-03-09T13:42:30.050Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "The --at flag uses 0-based indexing (CS standard). Keep it that way. When users say 'move to position 3' or 'make it third', the agent should translate to --at 2. The workflow layer handles the human-friendly ↔ programmatic mapping, not the CLI.",
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "30059067",
      "title": "Branding",
      "created": "2026-03-08T10:38:08.550Z",
      "archived": false,
      "body": "Product identity, positioning, and messaging.",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "8d82eaf8",
          "title": "Positioning",
          "created": "2026-03-08T10:35:15.956Z",
          "archived": false,
          "body": "Burrow fills the niche between too little and too much. Simple by design. Not a database, not a bare file. Just enough structure for agents to stay organized without overhead.",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "id": "fb15dc7b",
          "title": "Security & Privacy Awareness",
          "created": "2026-03-08T10:48:35.545Z",
          "archived": true,
          "body": "The burrow file lives in the repo — anything stored in cards is in git history forever. The agent should: (1) never put API keys, secrets, or sensitive data in cards, (2) warn users if card content looks sensitive, (3) treat cards as public-by-default. Same risk as hardcoding an API key — users should know, and the agent should actively guard against it.",
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
